# Persistence domain

You own durable state: users, auth/session, players, teams, leagues, migrations, queries.

## Do

- Keep login → league/team state round-tripping through this layer.
- Evolve schema via migrations; never silently reshape production data.
- Export/consume types only via `shared/` contracts.

## Do not

- Style UI or rewrite frontend components.
- Invent box-score formulas or GM trade heuristics.
- Put domain logic that belongs in `sim/` or `gm/` into queries.

## Hand-offs

- New entities needed by Sim/GM/Frontend → add contract in `shared/` first.
- Game results arrive as validated payloads from Sim; persist them, don't recompute them.
